<h3>8. Earn Backlinks Through Linkable Content</h3>
<p>Backlinks remain the strongest off-page ranking signal. But link building in 2026 is about creating content worth linking to, not mass outreach.</p>
<p><strong>How to implement:</strong> Publish original research, data studies, and definitive guides. Create free tools. Write comparison posts that bloggers reference. Use <a href="/blog/haro-link-building/">HARO and journalist outreach</a> for high-authority mentions.</p>
<h3>9. Optimize for Local Search (If Applicable)</h3>
<p>46% of all Google searches have local intent. Local SEO is its own discipline with separate ranking factors: <a href="/glossary/gbp-optimization/">Google Business Profile</a>, <a href="/glossary/google-reviews/">reviews</a>, <a href="/blog/nap-consistency/">NAP consistency</a>, and local citations.</p>
<p><strong>How to implement:</strong> Claim your GBP. Choose the right <a href="/blog/gbp-categories-guide/">categories</a>. Post weekly. Respond to reviews within 24 hours. Build local citations. Create location-specific landing pages. Read our guide on <a href="/blog/improve-google-maps-ranking/">improving Google Maps rankings</a>.</p>
<h3>10. Track Rankings and Iterate Monthly</h3>
<p>SEO without measurement is guessing. Track rankings, traffic, and conversions monthly. Identify what works and do more of it. Identify what fails and fix or cut it.</p>
<p><strong>How to implement:</strong> Set up Google Search Console and Google Analytics. Track your target keywords weekly in <a href="/reviews/ahrefs/">Ahrefs</a> or <a href="/reviews/semrush/">Semrush</a>. Review top-performing and declining pages monthly. Update declining content.</p>
